<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1801/425369-625x325.jpg?2" alt="Woolworths shares fall almost 10% after poor HEPS forecast" width="625" height="325" align="left">Woolworths said it expected to report on 22 February that HEPS for the 26 weeks to 24 December declined between 12.5% and 17.5%.The group's overall sales for the 26 weeks to 24 December grew just 2.5%, failing to keep pace with inflation.Woolworths' best performer was its South African food section which grew sales 9.4%, while its fashion, beauty and home section suffered a 0.2% decline in sales.The group expanded the retail space of its food stores by 6.8% from the matching period in 2016. Excluding the added retail space, food sales grew 5.3%.<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1801/425014-120x120.jpg?2" alt="Woolworths adds Balmain brand" width="120" height="120">Woolworths adds Balmain brandClothing and food retailer Woolworths is looking to bolster sales in the struggling Australian unit by adding the Balmain brand to its offerings...By Michelle Gumede 11 Jan 2018Its fashion, beauty and home section increased its space by 3.6%. Excluding the new space, sales fell 3.4%.Its Australian department store chain, David Jones, reported a 3.8% decline in total sales. It reduced David Jones's retail space 2.2% during the first half of its financial year.Its other Australian chain, Country Road, increased sales 5.2%.Source: BDpro